For the JIRA UI, JRA-44558 expresses the need to filter projects by field. For the API, [a question on Answers|https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/30934337/how-to-queryfilter-a-list-of-jira-projects-by-entity-properties] expresses a similar need.

As an add-on developer (for both Cloud and Server), I want to make an add-on effective only for a whitelist of projects so that user can decide which JIRA projects will have additional UI. I want to store the selection as entity properties on Projects. Later, I want to issue a single REST API request to recall the projects with my specific property. When I don't have this ability, I have to store the data at the add-on level, which means my array of "enabled projects" can get out of date with the project keys. It's also harder to maintain cross-platform (Cloud vs Server) data since I have different strategies for storing the data.

