I like the [inline comment|https://confluence.atlassian.com/conf57/commenting-on-pages-and-blog-posts-701435207.html#Commentingonpagesandblogposts-Addaninlinecomment] feature of Confluence, and with certain content it works extremely well to provide pointed feedback.  Why shouldn't we be able to comment in the same way on JIRA fields that contain text?  I'm currently in a feedback loop of clarifying with BA about very specific details of requirements written in a Description field, and I continually find the need to send emails with questions about screenshotted & highlighted "what do you mean by this bit", or in some cases where I believe there is a typo but I need to be sure (because in some cases either would be valid), I'll do that sort of email, and highlight a single character with an arrow and "do you actually mean....".  It'd be really handy for me to be able to highlight sections, with their corresponding comments/questions inline, and when the BA answers them, in many cases the bit she needs to alter is highlighted for her already.  It's win-win.

I can see that this _may_ conflict with the click-to-edit functionality, however a brief test tells me that technically, a double-click to highlight does not currently engage edit mode (a single click does), and therefore it should be able to be added, even if this feature was configurable.

Let me know what you think.
